            <title>[ELY-131] Add support for the creation of signed certificates.</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ELY-131</link>
                <project id="12315320" key="ELY">WildFly Elytron</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Whilst the standard Java APIs support the creation of public and private keys these APIs do not have a mechanism for creating a signed certificate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The latest RFC describing the format of these certificates is here: -&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;a href=&quot;https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc5280/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc5280/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Essentially this is about DER encoding of a number of fields combined with signing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The alternative could to being in something like bouncy castle.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
